description:
ArtEZ Institute of the Arts, visual arts, design, fashion, writing, music, dance, theater, architecture and interior design and teacher training.

ArtEZ Press publishes works derived from the ArtEZ Institute of the Arts. By publishing books ArtEZ Press wants to stimulate research within the various disciplines of art. These publications provide the opportunity to demonstrate the knowledge and skills in art, culture and education. Some publications may be used as teaching material, not just in the Netherlands but internationally.

Additionally these publications are intended for everyone with any interest in culture and/or art.
name: ArtEZ Press

description:
“Comics are words and pictures. You can do anything with words and pictures.” – Harvey Pekar

At 8th Wonder Press, Harvey Pekar’s words aren’t just wishful thinking, they’re an inspiration. At a time when most comics are rehashing, relaunching, or rebooting the same old ideas, we want to see something new, and we think you do too. We want to draw inspiration from the classics and take them into the future, fusing new ideas with the anything-goes spirit that hooked us all on comics in the first place.

We firmly believe that there is a comic for every person and a person for every comic. We want to make the comics culture a bigger place, getting more books into the hands of more readers and helping more creators get their comics into those hands.
name: 8th Wonder Press

deck: Imprint of IDW founded by Jeff Kline.
description:
Darby Pop Publishing was founded in 2013 by television writer/producer Jeff Kline (Transformers: Prime, Transformers: Robots in Disguise, Transformers: Rescue Bots, G.I. Joe: Renegades, Jackie Chan Adventures).

Darby Pop Publishing releases predominantly creator-owned titles as an extension of Kline's eclectic production company, Darby Pop Productions. Darby Pop′s current distribution partner is IDW Publishing, and Darby Pop was IDW′s first original-i.p. imprint. Cover artists have included: Howard Chaykin, Bernard Chang, Jose Lopez, Tony Fleecs, Tommy Lee Edwards, and Eisner Winner Andrew Robinson.

To date, all books published by the company have been written and created by film and television writer/producers, prompting Kline to remark that "Everyone in comics wants to break into Hollywood, but we're breaking Hollywood into comics."
name: Darby Pop
